    <h3>Area Selection</h3>
    <p>We are interested in an event happening in Innsbruck (Austria). It is good practice to first select the area of interest by opening the "Tools" panel, selecting the bbox (square) tool, clicking on the map to start drawing a rectangle and clicking on a point again to stop drawing. Creating a boundign box reduces the amount of data that needs to be loaded, only fetching the area you are interested in. We have created an exemplary selection already for you.</p>
</section>
<section data-timedomain="2020-01-06T00:00:00Z/2020-03-15T23:59:00Z">
